zhoneVoiceSignalingMib.description: The Zhone Voice Signaling MIB defines Zhone Voice Signaling specfic information. This MIB contains system side voice specific info, like the hookflash timers. User will not create this profile, but when system comes up, it checks to see if the scalar info exists. If not, it creates one with default values.

zhoneVoiceSignalingTimers.name: zhoneVoiceSignalingTimers
zhoneVoiceSignalingTimers.description: This is a place holder to contain all the system wide voice specific timers. 'hookFlashTimerMin' field is read/write field so a user can set this field to a particular value. It specifies the minimum timer for hookflash. 'hookFlashTimerMax' field is a read/write field to a user can set this field to a particular value. It specifies the maximum timer for hookflash.

hookFlashTimerMin.name: hookFlashTimerMin
hookFlashTimerMin.description: The Hookflash specifies the minimum timer that qualifies for a hookflash. Any loopopen below this time will be ignored as a glitch.

hookFlashTimerMax.name: hookFlashTimerMax
hookFlashTimerMax.description: The Hookflash specifies the maximum timer that qualifies for a hookflash. Any loopopen more than this timer will be considered as a onhook.

sysPartialDialTo.name: sysPartialDialTo
sysPartialDialTo.description: This object contains the maximum value of the partial dial time out.

sysCriticalDialTo.name: sysCriticalDialTo
sysCriticalDialTo.description: This object contains the maximum value of the critical \ dial time out.

sysBusyToneTo.name: sysBusyToneTo
sysBusyToneTo.description: This object contains the default timeout value for busy tone.

sysDialToneTo.name: sysDialToneTo
sysDialToneTo.description: This object contains the default timeout value for dial tone.

sysMsgWaitToneTo.name: sysMsgWaitToneTo
sysMsgWaitToneTo.description: This object contains the default timeout value for message wait tone.

sysOffhookWarnToneTo.name: sysOffhookWarnToneTo
sysOffhookWarnToneTo.description: This object contains the default timeout value for offhook warn tone.

sysRingingTo.name: sysRingingTo
sysRingingTo.description: This object contains the default timeout value for ringing.

sysRingbackTo.name: sysRingbackTo
sysRingbackTo.description: This object contains the default timeout value for ringback tone.

sysReorderToneTo.name: sysReorderToneTo
sysReorderToneTo.description: This object contains the default timeout value for reorder tone.

sysStutterToneTo.name: sysStutterToneTo
sysStutterToneTo.description: This object contains the default timeout value for stutter tone.

sysServerMaxTimer.name: sysServerMaxTimer
sysServerMaxTimer.description: This object is used as part of a retransmission algorithm when communicating with a call agent. This object contains the maximum time in seconds since the sending of the initial datagram to a call agent. If more than pktcNcsEndPntConfigTSMax time has elapsed, the endpoint becomes disconnected.

sysConfigMax1.name: sysConfigMax1
sysConfigMax1.description: This object contains the suspicious error threshold for signaling messages. The configMax1 object indicates the retransmission threshold at which the gateway MAY actively query the domain name server (DNS) in order to detect the possible change of call agent interfaces.

sysConfigMax2.name: sysConfigMax2
sysConfigMax2.description: This object contains the disconnect error threshold for signaling messages. The configMax2 object indicates the retransmission threshold at which the gateway SHOULD contact the DNS one more time to see if any other interfaces to the call agent have become available.

sysMax1Enable.name: sysMax1Enable
sysMax1Enable.description: This object enables/disables the Max1 domain name server (DNS) query operation when the configMax1 threshold has been reached.

sysMax2Enable.name: sysMax2Enable
sysMax2Enable.description: This object enables/disables the Max2 domain name server (DNS) query operation when the configMax2 threshold has been reached.

sysMaxWaitingDelay.name: sysMaxWaitingDelay
sysMaxWaitingDelay.description: Maximum Waiting Delay (MWD) contains the maximum number of seconds a Gateway waits after powering on, before initiating the restart procedure with the call agent.

sysDisconnectWaitTimer.name: sysDisconnectWaitTimer
sysDisconnectWaitTimer.description: This object contains the initial number of seconds the gateway waits after a disconnect, before initiating the disconnected procedure with the call agent.

sysDisconnectMinTimer.name: sysDisconnectMinTimer
sysDisconnectMinTimer.description: This object contains the minimum number of seconds the gatway waits after a disconnect, before initiating the disconnected procedure with the call agent.

sysDisconnectMaxTimer.name: sysDisconnectMaxTimer
sysDisconnectMaxTimer.description: This object contains the maximum number of seconds the gatway waits after a disconnect, before initiating the disconnected procedure with the call agent.

sysMaxRetransmitTimer.name: sysMaxRetransmitTimer
sysMaxRetransmitTimer.description: This object contains the maximum number of seconds for the retransmission timer. When this timer expires the gateway retransmits the message.

sysInitRetransmitTimer.name: sysInitRetransmitTimer
sysInitRetransmitTimer.description: This object contains the initial number of seconds for the retransmission timer.

sysKeepAliveTimer.name: sysKeepAliveTimer
sysKeepAliveTimer.description: Specifies a timeout value in minutes for sending long duration call notification message.

sysNoResponseTimer.name: sysNoResponseTimer
sysNoResponseTimer.description: Timeout period in seconds before no response is declared.

sysCallWaitMaxRepeat.name: sysCallWaitMaxRepeat
sysCallWaitMaxRepeat.description: This object contains the default value of the maximum number of repetitions of the call waiting tone that the gateway will play.

sysCallWaitDelay.name: sysCallWaitDelay
sysCallWaitDelay.description: This object contains the delay between repetitions of the call waiting tone that the gateway will play.

sysPulseInterDigitTimer.name: sysPulseInterDigitTimer
sysPulseInterDigitTimer.description: This is the pulse dial inter-digit timeout.

sysMinMakePulseWidth.name: sysMinMakePulseWidth
sysMinMakePulseWidth.description: This is the minimum make pulse width for the dial pulse.

sysMaxMakePulseWidth.name: sysMaxMakePulseWidth
sysMaxMakePulseWidth.description: This is the maximum make pulse width for the dial pulse.

sysMinBreakPulseWidth.name: sysMinBreakPulseWidth
sysMinBreakPulseWidth.description: This is the minimum break pulse width for the dial pulse.

sysMaxBreakPulseWidth.name: sysMaxBreakPulseWidth
sysMaxBreakPulseWidth.description: This is the maximum break pulse width for the dial pulse.
